ow?<br><br>Thank you for your help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/udonleeann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DonLeeAnn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/religion/angeleyz_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Friendly Shoulder</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#000000>(2/9/02 5:36:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gifs.net/animate/peaceglobe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Could use some advice</span><hr size=1> My personal opinion is that she should do what's in her heart - make things right for herself so she has no regrets.   <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb.html" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/2002/02/01/flamingtext_com_1012599151_27555.jpg" border=0 alt="Image by FlamingText.com"></a><br>Image by <a href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb2.html">FlamingText.com</a></BODY></HTML> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/uwolfgirlhk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfgirlhk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Friendly Shoulder</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#000000>(2/9/02 6:57:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.softcom.net/users/daniel1/Lisa2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Could use some advice</span><hr size=1> I don't know of anywhere online to help, as I've only recently found this site.<br><br>I guess my advice would be to ask her if confronting him would make her feel better, or if she thinks it would accomplish anything. Like Donna said, no regrets. If it will help her healing process, then maybe she should. But if it will cause her whole family to turn against her (as mine did), then maybe she shouldn't.<br><br>Is she seeing someone (not a psychiatrist), or able to discuss this openly with anyone? <p>________________________________________ <BR>I do not like this word "bomb." It is not a bomb. It is a device that is exploding.<BR>~French ambassador to New Zealand Jacques le Blanc, regarding press coverage of France's nuclear weapons tests in the Pacific</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/uflamestarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flamestarr</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.connect.usq.edu.au/students/d9817331/fire404.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Friendly Shoulder</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#000000>(2/9/02 7:14:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Could use some advice</span><hr size=1> She should do what is right for her..<br><br>personal Opinion is she should confront him!!! He Knows what he did to her !!! he wont be surprised...  Why should he go in peace after leading his granddaughter into the 7th circle of hell on earth...<br><br>It will free her from the inner guilt she feels... though she should feel no guilt!!! Victums always do exhibit a degree if &quot;it was my fault&quot;<br><br>And for the record <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I am a Phd in Personailty and Social Psychology with a masters in Criminal / abnormal psych <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoti